<p><u>
What is the Best Pet?<br>
</u>I often get tells from young magicians. Many of these wide-eyed mages have the
same question: &quot;What is the best pet?&quot; There is no universal best pet.
Magician pets are situational and have important differences:</p>
<div align="center">
  <center>
  <table border="1" width="80%">
    <tr>
      <td>
Earth</td>
      <td>Earth pets are made of dirt and rock. They are hearty pets with more health than
any other type of pet. However, earth pets take more of a beating since it isn't
very agile. Earth pets cast root on their targets once every 6 seconds. Root
holds the target in place, but also causes the Earth pet to take more damage in
a fight since a fleeing mob will turn and fight if it is rooted. At this level,
the root does not do damage. Earth pets are very resistant to disease.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>
Water</td>
      <td>Water pets have roughly 85% of the hit points of Earth. Water is more agile and
does not root an opponent, so it takes less overall damage in a fight. Water
casts a direct damage spell on its target every 6 seconds. Overall, Water does
more damage to its target than does Earth. Water pets are very resistant to
poison.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Air</td>
      <td>
Air pets have roughly 80% of the hit points of Earth. Air is the most agile of
all pets and it has the best AC. Further, it casts a stun on its target every 12
seconds. Since this pet is agile and stuns its opponent, it takes the least
damage of any pet in combat. The stun cast by the Air pet can interrupt casting.
Air pet stuns do not do damage at this level. Air pets have the annoying habit
of turning themselves invisible.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Fire</td>
      <td>
Fire pets have approximately 70% of the hit points of Earth. Fire is the least
hearty of the elementals. However, Fire pets cast a direct damage spell every 6
seconds and buff themselves with a fire shield. The self-buffed shield does
damage to an attacker on every hit. Since this damage is not resistible, Fire
will do more damage to a mob in a given period of time than any other pet. Fire
pets are immune to fire damage.</td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  </center>
</div>
<p><i>
History Lesson: Elementals used to be very different than they are today. For
example, only Fire and Water used to cast damage spells. Pets used to attack at
different speeds. Pets used to benefit greatly from weapons they were given.
Monsters used to attack a pet even if they would not have dared attack you. (A
benefit of the air pet used to be that it would turn itself invisible and
therefore most likely not cause of a fight. On PVP servers, an air pet's
invisibility may be of use still.) If you see information on the web that
contradicts what I've said above, it is likely out of date. It's also possible
that this document is out of date. This document was written in June of 2002.</i></p>
<p>
So what is the best pet? For mobs that hit hard and slow, Earth makes a good
choice. For mobs that hit fast, Fire is a good choice (mobs burn themselves to
death on the pet's fire shield). For mobs that cast spells, Air is a good choice
since it interrupts spell casts. Water is a good choice when you do not want the
pet to root. (Later, Water becomes more specialized than it is at this level).</p>
<h3>Pet Commands</h3>
<p>
